<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[317,1271,436,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
– Additional features to the two 
<collectingMunicipality box="[390,458,696,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Korean</collectingMunicipality>
males: (1) antenna with 31–32 antennomeres; (2) head in dorsal view twice broader than long, temple beyond eye slightly swollen; (3) legs dark reddish yellow, coxae darkening. 
<collectingCounty box="[1141,1215,724,745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Turning</collectingCounty>
up of the female sex the 
<specimenCount box="[496,592,753,774]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NIXON" authorityYear="1954" box="[668,757,753,774]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Antrusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaenia">
<emphasis box="[668,757,753,774]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. vaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may prove to represent a new species.
</paragraph>
